                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On July 5, 1951, the Board of Directors of the Export-Import Bank authorized a
                    line of credit amounting to $650,000 in favor of Fermirt Malaga Santolalla e
                    Hijos Negociación Agricola y Minera, S. A., of Lima, to assist in financing the
                    purchase of equipment and services, required for the expansion of facilities for
                    the production of tungsten at the company’s mines (Export-Import Bank of
                    Washington, <hi rend="italic">Thirteenth Semiannual Report to Congress for the
                        Period July–December 1951</hi>, Washington, 1952, pages 16–17,40).</p>
            </div>
        </body>
